#. </p><p>
msgctxt "sn35.147:0.2"
msgid "15. Navapurāṇavagga"
msgstr "15. The Old and the New"

#. </p><h1>
#. VAR: 147. Aniccanibbānasappāyasutta → sappāyasuttaṃ (bj) | sappāya 1 (pts1)
msgctxt "sn35.147:0.3"
msgid "147. Aniccanibbānasappāyasutta"
msgstr "147. The Impermanent as Conducive to Extinguishment"

#. </h1></div><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli4.134"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc1"></a>
msgctxt "sn35.147:1.1"
msgid "“Nibbānasappāyaṃ vo, bhikkhave, paṭipadaṃ desessāmi."
msgstr ""
"“Mendicants, I will teach you a practice that’s conducive to extinguishment."

msgctxt "sn35.147:1.2"
msgid "Taṃ suṇātha … pe …"
msgstr "Listen …"

msgctxt "sn35.147:1.3"
msgid "katamā ca sā, bhikkhave, nibbānasappāyā paṭipadā?"
msgstr "And what is that practice that’s conducive to extinguishment?"

msgctxt "sn35.147:1.4"
msgid ""
"Idha, bhikkhave, bhikkhu cakkhuṃ aniccanti passati, rūpā aniccāti passati, "
"cakkhuviññāṇaṃ aniccanti passati, cakkhusamphasso aniccoti passati. Yampidaṃ "
"cakkhusamphassapaccayā uppajjati vedayitaṃ sukhaṃ vā dukkhaṃ vā "
"adukkhamasukhaṃ vā tampi aniccanti passati … pe …"
msgstr ""
"It’s when a mendicant sees that the eye, sights, eye consciousness, and eye "
"contact are impermanent. And they see that the painful, pleasant, or neutral "
"feeling that arises conditioned by eye contact is also impermanent."

msgctxt "sn35.147:1.5"
msgid ""
"jivhā aniccāti passati, rasā aniccāti passati, jivhāviññāṇaṃ aniccanti "
"passati, jivhāsamphasso aniccoti passati, yampidaṃ jivhāsamphassapaccayā "
"uppajjati vedayitaṃ sukhaṃ vā dukkhaṃ vā adukkhamasukhaṃ vā tampi aniccanti "
"passati … pe …"
msgstr "They see that the ear … nose … tongue … body …"

msgctxt "sn35.147:1.6"
msgid ""
"mano aniccoti passati, dhammā aniccāti passati, manoviññāṇaṃ aniccanti "
"passati, manosamphasso aniccoti passati, yampidaṃ manosamphassapaccayā "
"uppajjati vedayitaṃ sukhaṃ vā dukkhaṃ vā adukkhamasukhaṃ vā tampi aniccanti "
"passati."
msgstr ""
"mind, thoughts, mind-consciousness, and mind contact are impermanent. And "
"they see that the painful, pleasant, or neutral feeling that arises "
"conditioned by mind contact is also impermanent."

msgctxt "sn35.147:1.7"
msgid "Ayaṃ kho sā, bhikkhave, nibbānasappāyā paṭipadā”ti."
msgstr "This is that practice that’s conducive to extinguishment.”"

#. </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "sn35.147:1.8"
msgid "Dutiyaṃ."
msgstr ""
